CIX: ChatGPT Custom Command-Line
Usage: [command] [options]

System Controls:
  --boot							Access splash screen
  --start         		Open ChatGPT
  -rst            		Restart system
  --r             		Check if ChatGPT is running
  --ver          			Show CIX version
  --unp								Download CIX in ChatGPTâ€™s memory
  --install						install CIX
  --deploy						Verify completion 


Memory Management:
  --um            		Update memory
  -nm <text>     			Input text
  -re <text>     			Remove text
  -re								  remove

Interaction:
  --ask           		Send query to ChatGPT
  --c-gpt         		Reference ChatGPT itself
  --res           		Get ChatGPT response
  Y or n          		Yes / No input

Customization & Syntax:
  --cg            		Change syntax
  --tl <title>   			Set title
  -a              	  Access modify mode

